external_knowledge:
- Mortality rate refers to the number of deaths in a given area or population over a certain period of time, often expressed as deaths per 1,000 individuals per year; 
- 'United States' refers to the country; 
- '2020' refers to the year of the data; 
- 'Male' refers to the sex of the demographic segment.

Culprits here refer to causes of death; 
Claiming lives here means causing death; 
Average toll here means average mortality rate.

sql:
SELECT md.*, loc.location_name 
FROM mortality_data md 
JOIN locations loc ON md.location_id = loc.location_id;
